HEADWORD: Dermestes
<hw>Der*mes"tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>dermhsth`s</grk>; <grk>de`rma</grk> skin + root of
<grk>'esthi`ein</grk> to eat.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
coleopterous insects, the larv⟦ae⟧ of which feed animal substances. They
are very destructive to dries meats, skins, woolens, and furs. The most
common species is <spn>Dermestes lardarius</spn>, known as the
<stype>bacon beetle</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dermestoid</ent>⟦br⟧
